// In selection sort, we compare the first element with all others and then do a swap if there is smallest element than the selected one's and in next iteration perform the stepa with next elements.
class SelectionSort{
    public static void main(String[] args){
        int[] arr = {5,4,3,2,1};
        for(int i = 0;i < arr.length-1;i++){
            int min = i;
            for(int j = i + 1;j < arr.length;j++){
                if(arr[min] > arr[j]) min = j;
            }
            int temp = arr[i];
            arr[i] = arr[min];
            arr[min] = k;
        }
    }
}
* It is an inplace algorith and doesn't require as much swapping as bubble sort does.
